Job Title: Project Manager   
  
Position Summary  
As a Project Manager, you will act as the bridge between our customers and development team. Your 
role is crucial in ensuring projects are delivered on time, within scope, and with the highest quality. You'll coordinate closely with both external stakeholders and internal teams to turn ideas into reality. ▪ 
Serve as the primary point of contact for customers, ensuring their requirements and 
expectations are understood and managed effectively. ▪ 
Collaborate with the development team to allocate tasks, monitor progress, and resolve 
issues. ▪ 
Plan and oversee project timelines, milestones, and deliverables using project management 
tools (preferably ClickUp). ▪ 
Facilitate regular communication and updates between stakeholders and developers. ▪ 
Identify risks and proactively implement mitigation strategies to keep projects on track. ▪ 
Document project progress, decisions, and lessons learned  
▪ 
Ensure that all projects are delivered on-time and within scope  
▪ 
Maintain regular communication with internal teams and stakeholders to provide project 
updates and gather feedback. ▪ 
Facilitate effective communication among team members and ensure everyone is aligned on 
project goals and objectives  
▪ 
Prepare and present project reports, status updates, and presentations to stakeholders as 
required  
▪ 
Assist in conducting user acceptance testing and capturing feedback for improvement  
▪ 
Assist in coordinating and organizing project meetings, including scheduling, agenda 
preparation, and meeting minutes  
▪ 
Foster a positive and collaborative team environment, promoting effective teamwork and 
knowledge sharing  
▪ 
Use and continually develop leadership skills

network

social media best practices
